list.item:
—In order to reestablish normal commercial intercourse with the
                                United States, Perú requires without delay five to six million
                                dollar credits;

—The Central Reserve Bank of Perú would apply to the amortization
                                of these credits the amount paid in dollars by United States
                                importers for Peruvian products;

Exeter, H. M. S., encounter with Graf Spee (see also Graf
              Spee
), 92, 96, 106, 108, 122
